WEBVTT

00:01.049 --> 00:02.465
<i>Previously on</i> Proven Innocent...

00:02.485 --> 00:03.967
JOE: <i>How you doing on Madeline Scott?</i>

00:03.985 --> 00:05.736
- Come on, I mean, it's not that bad.
- Oh, it's bad.

00:05.813 --> 00:06.904
I can't print this.

00:06.941 --> 00:08.804
- Okay, I will get you something.
- You better.

00:08.841 --> 00:09.945
Or someone else will.

00:09.982 --> 00:11.884
12 years ago, your opponent,
Esteban-Miller,

00:11.921 --> 00:13.789
represented Falcone on a series

00:13.826 --> 00:15.596
of corruption charges and won.

00:15.623 --> 00:17.331
I thought this was
your candidate of choice.

00:17.449 --> 00:19.248
Please believe that my being here means

00:19.285 --> 00:20.931
I was out of options.

00:20.983 --> 00:22.123
Toby Kissell?

00:22.160 --> 00:23.987
Keep your drug-addicted
brother away from me.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.999
Don't you come in here
like you're the innocent victim.

00:26.175 --> 00:28.318
You're a coward, and you're pathetic.

00:28.357 --> 00:29.849
<i>And everything that happened to him</i>

00:29.886 --> 00:31.636
<i>is your fault.</i>

00:32.661 --> 00:34.427
MADELINE: Fill out the form
in any language you like.

00:34.464 --> 00:35.716
Just tell us your story.

00:35.753 --> 00:37.240
- We'll try to help you if we can.
- All right.

00:37.277 --> 00:38.911
- VIOLET: We also have care packages
- Thank you.

00:38.948 --> 00:40.404
- with snacks and makeup
- Thank you.

00:40.441 --> 00:41.435
and hair care products.

00:41.472 --> 00:43.741
There's also a prepaid commissary card

00:43.778 --> 00:45.415
with a $20 credit.

00:45.542 --> 00:47.200
- Miss Scott. Do you know me?
- [GRUNTS]

00:47.237 --> 00:49.988
- WOMAN: Hey.
- Uh... yeah.

00:50.638 --> 00:53.269
You're... Adele Meyerson?

00:53.614 --> 00:55.415
I didn't kill my mother, Miss Scott.

00:55.452 --> 00:56.677
You got to believe me.

00:56.714 --> 00:58.263
I-I was wrongfully convicted
by the press,

00:58.318 --> 00:59.724
- just like you were.
- Okay. All right.

00:59.763 --> 01:01.295
Here's what I want you to do, Adele.

01:01.384 --> 01:03.451
Fill out this form, get it back
to me, and we'll review it.

01:03.524 --> 01:04.959
I-I can't stay here, okay?

01:04.995 --> 01:06.195
This place is a living nightmare.

01:06.232 --> 01:07.450
- I can't...
- Fill out the form.

01:07.470 --> 01:08.802
I'll review it personally.

01:08.921 --> 01:11.335
And I won't be swayed
by any of the past press.

01:11.546 --> 01:14.558
- Okay, thank you. I...
- Move out the way, bitch.

01:14.677 --> 01:16.469
They got $20 with my name on it.

01:16.506 --> 01:18.100
Oh, it's okay.
You can just step around.

01:18.137 --> 01:20.012
Why I got to step around
when she in my way?

01:20.623 --> 01:21.863
Hey!

01:22.293 --> 01:23.611
- Maddie.
- [ALARM BUZZING]

01:23.648 --> 01:25.796
[GRUNTING, SHOUTING]

01:26.428 --> 01:28.094
Hey, get off her.

01:33.945 --> 01:35.612
Don't even think about it.

01:37.633 --> 01:40.050
- You okay?
- Thank you.

01:42.293 --> 01:43.917
Want to put some ice on that, slugger?

01:43.954 --> 01:45.212
- Thank you.
- Yep.

01:45.249 --> 01:46.730
BODIE: Do you want me to
wrap your hand in a...

01:46.766 --> 01:48.146
a bag of frozen peas or something?

01:48.183 --> 01:49.793
Like Bradley Cooper in <i> A Star Is Born?</i>

01:50.011 --> 01:51.584
What does he have
that I don't have, huh?

01:51.621 --> 01:52.888
Are you asking that seriously?

01:52.925 --> 01:54.129
I didn't see it. How was it?

01:54.166 --> 01:55.971
I loved it. Why'd you skip it?

01:56.008 --> 01:58.277
I don't watch movies
with self-pitying white folks.

01:58.394 --> 02:00.596
So you haven't seen
a Julia Roberts movie since...?

02:00.777 --> 02:02.726
- [WHISPERING]: Never.
- Okay, I'm gonna jump in now.

02:02.796 --> 02:05.748
Uh, no, I don't need
a bag of frozen peas, thank you.

02:05.785 --> 02:07.597
Yes, I love Julia Roberts.

02:07.634 --> 02:11.285
And lastly, does anyone have
anything useful on Adele?

02:11.389 --> 02:12.638
Otherwise known as "CinderHella,"

02:12.675 --> 02:15.285
convicted of stabbing
her stepmother 37 times.

02:15.352 --> 02:16.528
VIOLET: <i>Adopted</i> mother.

02:16.565 --> 02:17.619
She was born in Korea

02:17.656 --> 02:19.550
and adopted by Taylor Meyerson,

02:19.587 --> 02:21.428
who's this billionaire textile magnate

02:21.465 --> 02:23.025
who brought her here
when she was six years old.

02:23.061 --> 02:25.064
EASY: Uh, the media says
Adele's adopted mother

02:25.101 --> 02:26.493
- never loved her.
- VIOLET: Well,

02:26.530 --> 02:27.723
she didn't speak English very well

02:27.760 --> 02:28.876
when she got here, so her mother

02:28.913 --> 02:30.790
ostracized her, called her stupid.

02:30.829 --> 02:32.159
EASY: She bonded with Daddy.

02:32.196 --> 02:34.838
He loved her, spoiled her,
and she loved him.

02:35.305 --> 02:36.706
I think her mother resented her because

02:36.726 --> 02:37.924
just after Daddy died...

02:37.961 --> 02:39.698
MADELINE: Adele got
treated like Cinderella.

02:39.735 --> 02:41.126
BODIE: Except for, in this fairy tale,

02:41.163 --> 02:42.681
CinderHella gets revenge.

02:42.718 --> 02:45.355
With a knife. 37 times.

02:45.449 --> 02:47.026
Adele swears she didn't do it.

02:47.063 --> 02:48.315
Oh, then she's definitely innocent.

02:48.352 --> 02:49.552
VIOLET: Yeah, because if she isn't,

02:49.588 --> 02:51.335
then she would be the first
convicted murderer

02:51.372 --> 02:53.018
to lie in the history
of American crime.

02:53.055 --> 02:55.597
Okay, your collective
trepidation is noted.

02:55.634 --> 02:58.003
But I remember the case
against her wasn't that strong.

02:58.040 --> 03:00.495
Did you hear the zombie-like 911 call?

03:00.541 --> 03:02.151
That's what convicted her
with the public.

03:02.188 --> 03:05.164
People didn't think my 911 call
was that great, either.

03:05.909 --> 03:07.753
<i>MADELINE [ON TAPE]: Please, help.</i>

03:07.790 --> 03:10.492
<i>She's not breathing.
There's so much blood.</i>

03:10.529 --> 03:12.480
<i>She's dead. Rosemary's dead.</i>

03:12.576 --> 03:14.362
[TAPE FAST-FORWARDING]

03:14.445 --> 03:15.761
You can't win.

03:15.798 --> 03:18.033
You're either too emotional
or not emotional enough.

03:18.070 --> 03:19.990
The only person who thought
I was telling the truth was...

03:20.026 --> 03:22.503
Was me... And just like you,
she contacted

03:22.540 --> 03:23.923
every innocence project she could.

03:23.960 --> 03:26.466
And... no one wanted to take her case,

03:26.503 --> 03:27.870
just like no one wanted to take mine.

03:27.907 --> 03:30.007
I love it when you two
go down memory lane.

03:30.044 --> 03:31.484
It's sweet, right?

03:31.521 --> 03:32.829
Should we go talk to Adele?

03:32.964 --> 03:34.496
Please.

03:36.350 --> 03:38.831
On this week's episode
of <i> Until Proven Innocent,</i>

03:38.868 --> 03:41.085
we will look at the case
of Adele Meyerson.

03:41.148 --> 03:44.483
It is a salacious tale
of greed and hate

03:44.529 --> 03:47.948
between an adopted daughter and
the mother who never loved her.

03:48.119 --> 03:50.754
In the famous novel <i>The Stranger,</i>

03:50.848 --> 03:52.698
the protagonist is convicted of murder

03:52.735 --> 03:56.696
mostly because he doesn't cry
at his mother's funeral.

03:56.776 --> 04:00.127
Sometimes, what we show
the world is more important

04:00.164 --> 04:01.565
than what is actually true.

04:01.625 --> 04:03.166
[BUZZER BLARES, LOCK CLICKS]

04:03.261 --> 04:05.221
911 OPERATOR [ON RECORDING]:
<i>911. What is your emergency?</i>

04:05.257 --> 04:06.897
ADELE: <i>My mother's
on the kitchen floor.</i>

04:07.114 --> 04:08.653
<i>There's blood.</i>

04:08.966 --> 04:10.190
<i>She's not moving.</i>

04:10.312 --> 04:11.770
911 OPERATOR: <i>Is she breathing?</i>

04:12.186 --> 04:13.986
ADELE: <i>She's dead.</i>

04:15.104 --> 04:17.072
I don't know why I sounded like that.

04:17.110 --> 04:19.353
I-I can't even remember calling 911.

04:19.391 --> 04:20.598
You were probably in shock.

04:20.635 --> 04:22.404
Do you remember finding
your mother's body?

04:22.441 --> 04:23.604
Kind of.

04:23.641 --> 04:26.951
I saw my mother, and there was
so much blood, I...

04:27.093 --> 04:29.201
something in my brain
just kind of shut off.

04:29.300 --> 04:31.010
After I found her, I couldn't sleep.

04:31.047 --> 04:33.327
I couldn't eat. I couldn't do anything.

04:33.364 --> 04:34.721
My aunt got so freaked out,

04:34.758 --> 04:36.675
she had me locked up in a mental ward.

04:36.786 --> 04:38.955
The case file says
you went in voluntarily.

04:38.992 --> 04:40.995
They make you say that
so they can keep you there

04:41.032 --> 04:42.489
over 48 hours.

04:42.596 --> 04:44.557
I missed my mother's funeral.

04:44.676 --> 04:46.425
I missed my best friend's funeral.

04:46.700 --> 04:49.066
They used it against me
at trial, said I was heartless.

04:49.103 --> 04:50.909
[SCOFFS] They did the same thing to me.

04:51.014 --> 04:52.847
It's a really common tactic.

04:52.965 --> 04:54.813
Especially when their case
isn't that strong.

04:54.850 --> 04:56.818
They convict you with
character assassination.

04:56.894 --> 04:58.852
The police did have physical evidence.

04:58.957 --> 05:00.332
They found bruising on your body

05:00.369 --> 05:02.000
consistent with a struggle.

05:03.004 --> 05:05.012
I know. And I can't explain that.

05:05.049 --> 05:06.849
I don't know how I got those bruises.

05:06.886 --> 05:08.246
You really can't remember?

05:08.290 --> 05:09.637
No...

05:09.815 --> 05:12.715
All these years later,
the whole thing is just a blur.

05:12.752 --> 05:14.318
The bruises were just there.

05:14.431 --> 05:16.082
What about the witness statements?

05:16.152 --> 05:17.941
Half your family members
testified against you.

05:18.004 --> 05:21.348
A lot of people lied,
for a lot of different reasons.

05:21.449 --> 05:23.785
They wanted her inheritance,
so they pinned it

05:23.822 --> 05:26.170
on the adopted Korean girl
who hated her mother.

05:26.207 --> 05:27.946
Why'd you hate her?

05:28.380 --> 05:30.564
Because she hated me.

05:30.948 --> 05:33.035
The CinderHella thing
is partially true.

05:33.072 --> 05:37.282
She treated me like her personal slave.

05:38.051 --> 05:40.243
You're not exactly convincing us
you didn't do it.

05:40.280 --> 05:41.793
I wasn't perfect,

05:41.902 --> 05:43.551
and my mother and I, we fought a lot,

05:43.588 --> 05:46.923
but I-I wouldn't hurt her.
I would never hurt anybody.

05:46.960 --> 05:49.769
All right, Adele. We'll keep digging.

05:50.008 --> 05:52.035
And maybe we'll find a glass slipper.

05:52.378 --> 05:55.863
♪ ♪

