06:11.432 --> 06:12.541
VIOLET: <i>A story</i>

06:12.578 --> 06:14.954
is the most important part
of the trial.

06:15.033 --> 06:17.433
What happened?
What does the evidence say?

06:17.470 --> 06:18.666
What's truth?

06:18.703 --> 06:19.878
And what is fiction?

06:19.971 --> 06:21.588
As wrongful conviction advocates,

06:21.625 --> 06:25.369
we know that the best place to
start retelling that story

06:25.494 --> 06:27.572
is with the original trial lawyer.

06:27.691 --> 06:29.775
Well, we know the case
is a little thin,

06:29.812 --> 06:31.643
but anything you can offer would help.

06:31.704 --> 06:34.104
It only took the cops and
the prosecutors about a week.

06:34.141 --> 06:35.682
They rushed the DNA,

06:35.869 --> 06:37.533
they didn't canvass all the witnesses,

06:37.570 --> 06:39.471
but had their theory, and that was it.

06:39.508 --> 06:41.190
Their theory being a bratty adopted kid

06:41.227 --> 06:42.627
who killed the mother
who never loved her.

06:42.663 --> 06:44.160
Yeah, but don't forget about the money.

06:44.259 --> 06:46.572
If Jane's dead,
Adele gets $300 million.

06:46.609 --> 06:49.079
- And now?
- Her father's sister got it all.

06:49.116 --> 06:50.431
Adele's Aunt Tessa.

06:50.669 --> 06:52.210
Is Aunt Tessa capable of murder?

06:52.305 --> 06:53.391
I don't know.

06:53.428 --> 06:55.513
She did get Adele locked up
in the mental hospital

06:55.590 --> 06:56.923
right after the murder.

06:57.126 --> 06:59.548
I see you got the murder weapon
DNA kicked at trial.

06:59.585 --> 07:01.439
Yeah, cops botched that pretty good.

07:01.476 --> 07:04.634
The entire case came down
to eyewitnesses and motive.

07:04.825 --> 07:07.699
Also, the jury just loved
to hate Adele.

07:08.290 --> 07:09.405
Hmm.

07:09.442 --> 07:10.749
She was in shock.

07:10.786 --> 07:12.400
Well, she had just found
her dead mother.

07:12.437 --> 07:13.782
That seems relatively normal.

07:13.819 --> 07:16.798
- She was, for the most part.
- And the other parts?

07:16.929 --> 07:19.420
After a few days,
she became belligerent.

07:19.681 --> 07:21.256
Especially when she heard
she was missing

07:21.293 --> 07:22.667
her mother's funeral.

07:23.173 --> 07:25.160
We needed to use restraints.

07:25.478 --> 07:26.837
Well, if they had to use restraints,

07:26.874 --> 07:28.207
that would explain the bruising.

07:28.720 --> 07:30.838
Do you have pictures of Adele
when she was admitted?

07:30.875 --> 07:32.794
I'm not legally allowed to say.

07:32.831 --> 07:34.220
Well, we could get a court order.

07:34.257 --> 07:36.433
- I think you should.
- MADELINE: Are you saying that

07:36.470 --> 07:38.446
because you don't think Adele
killed her mother?

07:38.590 --> 07:40.606
To me, she was grieving.

07:40.720 --> 07:43.912
So, no, I don't believe
she killed her mother.

07:45.196 --> 07:46.447
MADELINE: We need to cast doubt

07:46.484 --> 07:48.058
on this bruising evidence.

07:48.095 --> 07:49.867
I'll subpoena the hospital records.

07:49.986 --> 07:52.095
They clearly have something
the doctor wants us to see.

07:52.211 --> 07:54.446
There's also eyewitness
testimony and some

07:54.483 --> 07:55.924
not-so-great character witnesses.

07:56.205 --> 07:57.872
Like this Aunt Tessa character.

07:58.070 --> 07:59.696
Who puts a kid in a mental hospital

07:59.733 --> 08:00.969
after their mother dies?

08:01.006 --> 08:03.340
A woman who inherited $300 million?

08:03.424 --> 08:06.693
Well, she's our number-one
suspect. Let's follow the money.

08:09.147 --> 08:10.729
Levi, what is it?

08:11.254 --> 08:13.230
Toby Kissell's dead.

08:13.712 --> 08:15.512
He hung himself.

08:21.991 --> 08:25.509
I can't believe it.
I mean, I just saw him.

08:25.567 --> 08:27.109
So did I.

08:28.212 --> 08:29.815
After you talked to him,

08:29.876 --> 08:32.294
he came here and threatened
to have you arrested.

08:33.644 --> 08:35.544
I threatened him back.

08:37.484 --> 08:39.167
Well, that's a relief.

08:39.284 --> 08:41.126
'Cause I thought I was the one
that drove him to suicide.

08:41.162 --> 08:42.875
It turns out you were.

08:43.515 --> 08:46.056
[BOTH LAUGH]

08:46.141 --> 08:48.309
- Thanks, Brother.
- Ah, yeah.

08:48.992 --> 08:50.984
This has got to be
about Rosemary, though.

08:51.080 --> 08:52.422
I mean, think about it, you know?

08:52.459 --> 08:54.742
We see him, he kills himself.

08:54.816 --> 08:56.124
He's feeling guilty.

08:56.161 --> 08:58.852
I mean, th-there's a reason
why he lied on the stand.

08:58.964 --> 09:01.024
Or he was depressed
and he killed himself

09:01.061 --> 09:03.087
because he needed help.

09:04.064 --> 09:05.446
We got to go to the funeral.

09:06.063 --> 09:08.438
Are you serious? Why?

09:08.938 --> 09:11.374
To find out what happened to Rosemary.

09:12.024 --> 09:14.541
Best place to start
is Toby Kissell's funeral.

09:15.155 --> 09:16.446
[GROANS SOFTLY]

09:17.530 --> 09:19.251
MAN [OVER P.A.]: <i>Traeger threesome,
hold up there.</i>

09:19.287 --> 09:21.016
<i>Lee single is gonna be joining you.</i>

09:22.326 --> 09:24.810
<i>Twosome, check in, please.
Bryer twosome, check in.</i>

09:27.164 --> 09:29.541
Whew! That is quite the stroke
you got there.

09:29.578 --> 09:31.168
I bet you're even better with a knife.

09:31.540 --> 09:33.656
- I beg your pardon?
- A knife.

09:33.693 --> 09:36.641
You know, like, uh,
like you'd use to stab somebody.

09:36.678 --> 09:38.777
Maybe 37 times or something.

09:41.886 --> 09:43.271
You're peculiar.

09:43.403 --> 09:45.353
- I don't like peculiar.
- Hmm.

09:45.390 --> 09:46.731
And you're Tessa Meyerson.

09:47.578 --> 09:50.036
I work for your adopted niece, Adele.

09:50.164 --> 09:52.345
You remember her, right?
You put her in an asylum

09:52.382 --> 09:54.220
right before you helped convict her?

09:54.418 --> 09:58.164
And then you inherited your late
brother's $300 million estate.

09:58.460 --> 10:00.017
Yeah, you had motive,

10:00.851 --> 10:02.467
you certainly have the strength.

10:02.538 --> 10:04.997
So you think that I killed Jane
and framed Adele?

10:05.343 --> 10:06.898
The thought crossed my mind.

10:07.059 --> 10:08.682
I loved Adele.

10:09.546 --> 10:11.664
She was the cutest little girl,

10:11.912 --> 10:14.270
but then she turned into
a horrible brat.

10:14.590 --> 10:17.679
Drove my brother Taylor into
an early grave with worry.

10:17.880 --> 10:19.544
Jane never liked her.

10:19.581 --> 10:22.508
So after Taylor died, she cut her off.

10:22.785 --> 10:25.069
That is why Adele murdered her.

10:25.882 --> 10:29.917
Believe me, I don't need money
as a motive.

10:30.360 --> 10:32.038
- Why is that?
- Sweetie,

10:32.258 --> 10:34.410
I was already rich.

10:40.848 --> 10:42.210
Oh, hey.

10:42.523 --> 10:44.437
I think Aunt Tessa might
just be the murderer.

10:44.546 --> 10:46.195
I confronted her, I went at her hard,

10:46.232 --> 10:48.223
and she responded with
ice-cold gin in her veins.

10:48.260 --> 10:50.226
Did she say anything incriminating?

10:50.429 --> 10:52.350
Yes, she said that she did it
for the money,

10:52.427 --> 10:54.344
that she was guilty,
that I should take her in.

10:54.381 --> 10:56.085
Violet, what have you got?

10:56.122 --> 10:59.023
Jane Meyerson was having
an affair with her lawyer.

10:59.060 --> 11:01.460
Rumor has it she called it off
just before she was murdered.

11:01.537 --> 11:03.987
Oh, man, that is good.
Where'd you get that from?

11:04.084 --> 11:05.562
A magical land called the Internet.

11:05.599 --> 11:07.582
But I confirmed it
with a reporter friend.

11:07.755 --> 11:10.506
Did the cops interview either of
these people for Jane's murder?

11:10.543 --> 11:12.570
Nope. They focused on Adele.

11:12.607 --> 11:14.603
BODIE: Two suspects
with perfect motives.

11:14.640 --> 11:16.040
Police don't even interview them.

11:16.419 --> 11:18.148
Maybe CinderHella is innocent.

11:18.185 --> 11:19.302
EASY: All this is good,

11:19.339 --> 11:21.437
but it's not gonna
get her conviction overturned.

11:21.578 --> 11:22.890
We need something definitive

11:22.927 --> 11:24.750
besides rumors and Bodie's bullying.

11:24.818 --> 11:27.020
The subpoena came in today
for Adele's hospital records.

11:27.057 --> 11:28.391
Might be something there.

11:28.428 --> 11:29.903
EVAN: Madeline.

11:31.341 --> 11:33.295
Mind if we talk?

11:35.914 --> 11:37.210
Sure, Evan.

11:37.441 --> 11:38.781
Yeah.

11:41.012 --> 11:42.921
[SIGHS]

11:43.463 --> 11:45.104
You sold me out.

11:45.562 --> 11:47.257
And to Bellows, of all people...

11:47.294 --> 11:50.875
And you suborned perjury
defending a corrupt cop.

11:51.094 --> 11:53.710
Exposing it got my
innocent client out of prison.

11:53.747 --> 11:55.801
And you teed up Bellows to win.

11:55.928 --> 11:58.093
I thought we were on the same team.

11:58.584 --> 12:01.718
What if I gave you the perfect
way to sink Rosemary's Law?

12:04.007 --> 12:05.914
Depends on how perfect it is.

12:05.976 --> 12:08.251
Rosemary's father hates Rosemary's Law.

12:08.288 --> 12:10.171
He thinks it's politically motivated.

12:10.296 --> 12:11.703
I bet he'd come out against it

12:11.740 --> 12:13.848
and then Bellows
can't use it against you.

12:15.343 --> 12:17.398
I'd be happy to broker an introduction.

12:17.435 --> 12:19.285
You'd be thrilled.

12:19.368 --> 12:22.531
You want to see Rosemary's Law
defeated just as much as I do.

12:22.613 --> 12:24.955
Politics is horrible, isn't it?

12:27.204 --> 12:29.015
Right this way. Yes.

12:30.023 --> 12:31.704
MAYFIELD: I think you
gentlemen know one another.

12:31.740 --> 12:32.580
[BELLOWS CHUCKLES]

12:32.617 --> 12:33.943
We've never officially met.

12:34.037 --> 12:35.875
- Gore Bellows.
- Rick Zahn.

12:35.912 --> 12:37.054
It's a pleasure.

12:37.210 --> 12:38.500
I'll leave you to it, then.

12:38.537 --> 12:40.295
- BELLOWS: Thank you.
- Thank you.

12:40.616 --> 12:41.866
What can I do for you?

12:41.903 --> 12:43.328
Just about to ask you the same thing.

12:43.379 --> 12:44.679
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

12:44.773 --> 12:48.717
Ah... Word is that
your campaign is, uh...

12:48.799 --> 12:49.956
fraught.

12:49.993 --> 12:51.777
Madeline Scott's nipping at your heels.

12:51.838 --> 12:53.429
I read recently that she's taking on

12:53.466 --> 12:56.259
yet another one of
your wrongful convictions.

12:56.296 --> 12:57.812
And through her work, she's writing

12:57.849 --> 13:00.458
a pretty persuasive narrative
of your incompetence.

13:00.495 --> 13:02.245
We are all over the Scott issue.

13:02.406 --> 13:04.961
Rosemary's Law has been
pretty effective

13:04.998 --> 13:06.414
in blunting her attacks on me.

13:06.451 --> 13:08.171
Your campaign staff
reached out to my people,

13:08.208 --> 13:10.555
so I was assuming that you
needed some financial help,

13:10.592 --> 13:11.871
but if that's not the case...

13:11.908 --> 13:13.482
No! No, no, I, uh...

13:13.519 --> 13:15.185
I need your support.

13:15.320 --> 13:16.718
And I understand

13:16.755 --> 13:19.617
that you need a friend in
the attorney general's office.

13:21.084 --> 13:22.882
And I'd like to be that friend.

13:22.965 --> 13:24.406
[ZAHN CHUCKLES]

13:24.569 --> 13:25.892
I appreciate the candor.

13:25.929 --> 13:27.835
I like someone
that just lays it out there.

13:27.977 --> 13:30.269
Then, by all means, tell me
what it is you're looking for

13:30.373 --> 13:31.497
in a candidate.

13:31.569 --> 13:32.844
I'm looking for help.

13:34.247 --> 13:35.858
Dorisole.

13:35.895 --> 13:38.265
It's a life-changing
appetite suppressant,

13:38.302 --> 13:40.019
and it's one of my most
successful products.

13:40.183 --> 13:41.945
It's so successful, I got four

13:41.982 --> 13:43.905
big pharma firms
trying to take it down.

13:44.023 --> 13:45.273
The FDA's investigating.

13:45.310 --> 13:47.046
At the behest of those same firms.

13:47.083 --> 13:48.476
I think you're probably aware there's a

13:48.513 --> 13:50.477
criminal investigation
being brought against me

13:50.514 --> 13:53.822
by some young, ill-advised
prosecutor downstate,

13:53.859 --> 13:56.914
so if I were to, uh,
back you and you won,

13:56.951 --> 14:00.003
I would just love it
if all that went away.

14:00.710 --> 14:02.901
It's a tremendous opportunity, Gore.

14:03.107 --> 14:05.617
You can ensure that
a life-saving product

14:05.654 --> 14:07.773
remains available
and, at the same time,

14:07.822 --> 14:09.588
earn the thanks of a constituency

14:09.625 --> 14:11.921
that has the means to bankroll you

14:12.010 --> 14:14.140
all the way to Springfield...

14:15.234 --> 14:16.562
Governor.

14:18.466 --> 14:20.132
You know...

14:21.000 --> 14:23.554
my granddad worked
the train yards for 40 years.

14:23.591 --> 14:25.361
Mm-hmm. And your father was a...

14:25.398 --> 14:27.976
a city alderman
of grand and noble purpose

14:28.013 --> 14:30.109
that never got above ward politics.

14:30.187 --> 14:32.671
Then you know the reason I want
to be the next attorney general.

14:32.855 --> 14:34.429
System's failing.

14:34.498 --> 14:36.056
Corruption is rampant.

14:36.298 --> 14:37.899
Honest and hard-working people
are missing out

14:37.935 --> 14:39.893
on what makes this country great.

14:40.255 --> 14:41.879
And I want to fix that.

14:44.826 --> 14:46.734
There's a lot I can do for you, Rick.

14:47.840 --> 14:50.265
But if Dorisole turns out
to be dangerous...

14:52.617 --> 14:54.439
...I can't help.

14:55.773 --> 14:57.378
Totally understand.

14:57.736 --> 14:59.345
And I'm sure none of this
will come to pass.

14:59.382 --> 15:01.875
Then, one day, we'll all
look back on this and laugh.

15:02.118 --> 15:04.460
- Hey, best of luck with the campaign.
- Thank you.

15:13.905 --> 15:15.225
[EXHALES]

15:15.674 --> 15:17.942
♪ ♪

15:20.958 --> 15:23.792
CinderHella's story is no fairy tale.

15:23.950 --> 15:27.359
Wrongful conviction lawyers pull
double duty as storytellers.

15:27.468 --> 15:29.901
We have to destroy
the prosecution's story

15:29.989 --> 15:32.748
and then tell a different,
more believable one.

15:33.116 --> 15:35.749
Adele wanted to attend
her mother's funeral,

15:35.844 --> 15:38.186
and when I told her
she couldn't, she got angry.

15:38.232 --> 15:41.334
Attending orderlies
had to restrain her.

15:41.641 --> 15:44.569
Were you present when
these police photos were taken?

15:44.608 --> 15:47.064
- Yes.
- And was that before or after

15:47.101 --> 15:48.702
Adele's altercation with your staff?

15:48.739 --> 15:49.930
It was after.

15:49.967 --> 15:52.391
I believe she sustained
those bruises at the hospital.

15:52.447 --> 15:54.438
MADELINE: But the
prosecution's entire case

15:54.475 --> 15:56.751
was based on the fact
that Adele got those bruises

15:56.788 --> 15:57.999
when she struggled with her mother.

15:58.036 --> 16:00.319
In my opinion, they were incorrect.

16:00.382 --> 16:01.671
Why didn't you tell investigators?

16:01.708 --> 16:03.124
REED: I did. I gave them my report

16:03.161 --> 16:06.007
and advised that
their time line was wrong.

16:07.016 --> 16:08.788
It's an obvious Brady violation,
Your Honor.

16:08.825 --> 16:10.967
Defense counsel was never given
this report.

16:11.030 --> 16:13.827
Mr. Duncan, was the prosecution
aware of this report?

16:13.864 --> 16:15.467
This wasn't my case, Your Honor.

16:15.504 --> 16:17.202
That doesn't answer my question.

16:18.142 --> 16:19.808
I'm sorry, it's the best I can do.

16:19.845 --> 16:21.350
Petitioner moves for a new trial,

16:21.387 --> 16:23.874
on the grounds of
prosecutorial misconduct.

16:24.280 --> 16:25.569
Motion granted.

16:25.613 --> 16:27.569
Defendant is remanded to the custody

16:27.606 --> 16:29.436
of the Cook County Correctional Center,

16:29.484 --> 16:31.382
but we'll calendar immediately.

16:32.737 --> 16:33.894
[QUIET MURMURING]

16:34.027 --> 16:35.735
EASY: New trial, new chance at freedom.

16:35.772 --> 16:36.972
- BAILIFF: Ready?
- EASY: All right.

16:37.008 --> 16:38.740
- Let's go.
- It's okay.

16:39.483 --> 16:41.223
Now we just have to win.

16:41.405 --> 16:43.141
Yeah, we got a problem.

16:43.203 --> 16:44.319
EASY: What's up?

16:44.378 --> 16:45.686
Aunt Tessa and Loverboy Lawyer

16:45.744 --> 16:47.744
both have airtight alibis
for the night of the murder.

16:48.444 --> 16:49.874
Neither of them did it.

16:50.034 --> 16:51.827
We have to find a new suspect.

16:57.522 --> 16:58.977
The judge granted you a new trial,

16:59.014 --> 17:00.702
but you're still charged with murder.

17:00.803 --> 17:01.952
We've been able to knock down

17:01.989 --> 17:03.223
one of the prosecution's theories,

17:03.260 --> 17:05.127
but we still need to find
a solid suspect.

17:05.202 --> 17:06.976
Tell us again about
the night of the murder.

17:07.012 --> 17:08.099
You were at a party.

17:08.137 --> 17:09.769
Yes, at my friend Sydney's house.

17:09.844 --> 17:11.503
And she testified for you at trial,

17:11.540 --> 17:13.053
said you were there all night.

17:13.089 --> 17:15.007
EASY: Uh, Grant Thargard,
a prosecution witness,

17:15.044 --> 17:16.194
said you left early.

17:16.232 --> 17:17.974
Grant lied, he's a liar.

17:18.012 --> 17:19.194
<i>[ECHOING]: He's a liar.</i>

17:19.231 --> 17:20.948
MAN: Toby Kissell, for the prosecution.

17:21.051 --> 17:23.318
Levi told me he was going
to kill Rosemary

17:23.515 --> 17:25.749
and that his sister was gonna help him.

17:25.990 --> 17:27.519
[WHISPERS]: I can't believe this.

17:27.704 --> 17:29.241
EASY: Why would he perjure himself?

17:29.288 --> 17:30.452
ADELE: I don't know.

17:30.489 --> 17:31.939
He tried to have sex
with me that night,

17:32.007 --> 17:33.207
and I wouldn't let him.

17:33.244 --> 17:34.467
But I don't think

17:34.504 --> 17:36.452
that's a reason
why he would ruin my life.

17:36.489 --> 17:38.389
Any reason to think he could
have killed your mother?

17:38.503 --> 17:39.913
He knew her.

17:40.288 --> 17:42.568
I guess it's possible.
I-I don't know. Why?

17:42.655 --> 17:45.225
All right, first, let's focus on
a motive for why he would lie.

17:45.279 --> 17:47.522
Is there anyone who would know?
Anyone we can talk to?

17:47.608 --> 17:49.892
Sydney Ball. It was her party.

17:50.749 --> 17:52.850
Me and Adele were best friends.

17:52.887 --> 17:55.913
I feel terrible I've never
visited her in prison.

17:56.183 --> 17:57.400
I miss her.

17:57.476 --> 17:59.397
It's hard to see
the people we love locked up,

17:59.434 --> 18:01.021
but you should visit her.

18:01.058 --> 18:02.274
It would totally make her day.

18:02.311 --> 18:04.960
I'll go see her. I feel bad.

18:05.162 --> 18:07.070
She's not a killer.

18:07.553 --> 18:10.428
But... I wouldn't blame her
if she did it.

18:10.524 --> 18:13.124
Her mom was such a bitch.

18:13.259 --> 18:15.522
She would always say Adele
was her adopted daughter.

18:15.596 --> 18:17.721
You know, stressing "adopted."

18:17.791 --> 18:20.041
Like we couldn't figure it out anyway.

18:20.082 --> 18:21.428
So what happened that night?

18:21.514 --> 18:23.889
My parents were out of town, so...

18:23.999 --> 18:25.377
I threw a party.

18:25.414 --> 18:27.327
<i>Me and Adele were having fun, so we</i>

18:27.364 --> 18:28.610
took some Molly.

18:28.647 --> 18:30.708
- How much?
- Too much.

18:31.086 --> 18:32.803
After a couple hours,

18:32.840 --> 18:34.903
she said she was feeling dizzy,

18:34.940 --> 18:36.423
so she went upstairs to sleep it off.

18:36.706 --> 18:38.113
Do you remember what time that was?

18:38.315 --> 18:39.672
I wish I did.

18:40.186 --> 18:41.499
<i>I was so messed up.</i>

18:41.643 --> 18:42.858
Grant Thargard testified

18:42.895 --> 18:44.803
that Adele left your house at midnight.

18:45.450 --> 18:47.397
You know any reason why
he would have lied about that?

18:47.434 --> 18:48.521
No.

18:48.558 --> 18:50.449
I mean, he's a total douchebag.

18:50.531 --> 18:52.005
That could be why.

18:52.257 --> 18:54.171
I assume you had a cell phone
back then, right?

18:54.208 --> 18:55.541
Did you take any pictures?

18:55.578 --> 18:57.514
I gave them all to Adele's lawyer,

18:57.551 --> 18:59.602
but she's not in any of the photos.

19:00.444 --> 19:02.233
Do you mind if we take a look at them?

19:02.297 --> 19:04.239
I just... I don't know,

19:04.276 --> 19:06.167
I feel like we might find
something they missed.

19:06.779 --> 19:08.091
So, like I said on the phone,

19:08.128 --> 19:11.822
<i>Until Proven Innocent</i> is like
a... a true crime podcast.

19:11.909 --> 19:14.452
So this is like...<i> Serial?</i>

19:14.489 --> 19:15.641
VIOLET: Yeah, sort of.

19:15.678 --> 19:17.085
But not as good.

19:17.256 --> 19:19.147
This week's episode
is about the Meyerson murder,

19:19.184 --> 19:21.538
and we wanted to get your take on it.

19:21.645 --> 19:22.695
Are you ready?

19:22.731 --> 19:24.569
Cool. Let's do it.

19:24.606 --> 19:27.018
So, Grant, what can you tell us
about the night

19:27.055 --> 19:28.717
that Jane Meyerson was murdered?

19:28.811 --> 19:30.238
Sydney had a big party.

19:30.275 --> 19:31.988
I was the... the D.D.

19:32.025 --> 19:34.191
Uh, designated driver.

19:34.323 --> 19:36.488
Adele was out of control.

19:36.602 --> 19:39.136
Her and Sydney took some Molly.
Adele came on to me.

19:39.173 --> 19:40.531
She came on to you?

19:40.802 --> 19:42.801
Big-time. I turned her down.

19:42.838 --> 19:44.905
I'm, uh, I'm not into lo mein.

19:45.004 --> 19:46.598
[STRAINED CHUCKLE]

19:49.580 --> 19:52.254
Uh, we actually heard that...
that you came on to Adele.

19:52.291 --> 19:54.224
You tried to, uh,
hook up with her that night.

19:54.413 --> 19:56.473
- Who the hell said that?
- Adele.

19:56.813 --> 19:58.965
You talked to her? In prison?

19:59.027 --> 20:00.198
How'd you manage that?

20:00.235 --> 20:02.090
Oh, we're on her defense team.

20:07.838 --> 20:09.394
I'm out of here.

20:10.866 --> 20:12.899
Oh, hey. One more thing.
Uh, we got you this.

20:12.936 --> 20:15.103
<i>Until Proven Innocent</i> T-shirt.

20:15.277 --> 20:16.941
It's also a subpoena.

20:17.418 --> 20:19.027
We'll see you in court.

20:24.113 --> 20:25.715
LEVI: Half our high school's here.

20:25.879 --> 20:26.990
MADELINE: Yep.

20:27.027 --> 20:28.625
So this should be fun.

20:29.072 --> 20:30.473
Or not.

20:30.715 --> 20:32.421
Who invited you guys?

20:32.458 --> 20:34.500
The whole class got an e-mail about it.

20:34.582 --> 20:36.017
We're here to pay our respects.

20:36.054 --> 20:37.269
Fine.

20:37.341 --> 20:39.051
Just don't kill anybody.

20:39.113 --> 20:40.813
Well, we'll see how the day goes.

20:44.855 --> 20:46.141
WOMAN: Oh, my gosh.

20:46.178 --> 20:47.725
Maddie and Levi Scott.

20:47.762 --> 20:50.855
- BOTH: Hi, Cassie.
- I haven't seen you two since...

20:50.918 --> 20:52.371
Our murder trial.

20:52.691 --> 20:54.715
Rosemary and Madeline
fought all the time.

20:54.790 --> 20:56.497
Madeline had a violent temper.

20:57.098 --> 20:58.395
I guess we got that one wrong,

20:58.432 --> 20:59.793
- huh?
- Yeah.

20:59.830 --> 21:01.075
So weird that we only see each other

21:01.112 --> 21:02.234
when someone dies.

21:02.340 --> 21:04.668
Levi Scott? Holy crap.

21:04.730 --> 21:07.496
You look good. Guess, uh,
prison agrees with you.

21:07.550 --> 21:08.924
Clint, right?

21:09.043 --> 21:11.191
Levi was always macking
on high school girls.

21:11.228 --> 21:12.527
He was a real perv.

21:12.564 --> 21:15.433
Wow. Yeah, you got bald.

21:16.359 --> 21:18.425
I guess freedom really
took a crap on you, huh?

21:18.462 --> 21:21.032
[LAUGHS] Always a jackass, huh, Levi?

21:21.175 --> 21:23.092
Yeah.

21:26.145 --> 21:29.087
This was a great idea.
Everyone's so happy to see us.

21:29.389 --> 21:31.243
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

21:32.545 --> 21:34.219
Yeah.

21:40.474 --> 21:42.407
Toby would feel so honored

21:42.444 --> 21:44.837
to see all of his
classmates here today.

21:44.995 --> 21:48.337
Hey, who's the
Girl with the Dragon Tattoo?

21:51.285 --> 21:53.180
I think that's Linda Barrett.

21:54.171 --> 21:57.648
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

21:58.329 --> 22:02.311
Wow. She was one of Heather's
mean girl flunkies.

22:03.463 --> 22:04.884
MINISTER: We will now hear from one

22:04.921 --> 22:08.931
of Toby's closest classmates,
Heather Dupinski-Husband.

22:09.061 --> 22:11.261
- Ugh, Lord.
- You kidding me?

22:11.912 --> 22:13.495
HEATHER: Thank you.

22:16.869 --> 22:18.035
[MICROPHONE FEEDBACK SQUEALS]

22:18.154 --> 22:21.478
Toby Kissell was preternaturally kind,

22:21.707 --> 22:25.370
- generous and empathetic.
- "Preternaturally"?

22:25.407 --> 22:27.353
- [CHUCKLES]
- HEATHER: Even after all these years,

22:27.390 --> 22:30.366
he never fully recovered
from the brutal slaying

22:30.454 --> 22:32.024
of his teenage love,

22:32.321 --> 22:35.027
my best friend, Rosemary Lynch.

22:35.271 --> 22:36.915
Her mur...

22:41.079 --> 22:43.571
Her murder devastated this town,

22:43.655 --> 22:45.747
and I know it haunted Toby.

22:48.529 --> 22:52.017
I have no doubt that this nightmare,

22:52.659 --> 22:55.642
which eventually led him
to take his own life,

22:56.884 --> 23:00.578
began the night
that Rosemary Lynch died.

23:01.376 --> 23:02.915
MADELINE: Linda?

23:03.082 --> 23:05.110
LINDA: Hey, Maddie.

23:05.745 --> 23:07.385
MADELINE: Ditched out on
Heather's eulogy, huh?

23:07.421 --> 23:09.280
I thought you two were pals.

23:09.380 --> 23:12.142
No. We are definitely not pals anymore.

23:12.262 --> 23:13.904
What happened?

23:15.419 --> 23:17.385
I was almost the third.

23:17.800 --> 23:19.817
The third what?

23:19.897 --> 23:22.501
Dead high school friend. Drugs.

23:23.235 --> 23:25.298
If the paramedics had been
a minute later,

23:25.344 --> 23:27.161
I wouldn't be standing here right now.

23:27.564 --> 23:30.282
Did you know about
this whole Adderall ring?

23:31.163 --> 23:32.626
Yeah.

23:33.462 --> 23:35.829
Heather would steal
her dad's prescription pad,

23:35.866 --> 23:39.235
and Toby sold it.
Some of us got it for free.

23:39.337 --> 23:41.393
Friends of Heather's?

23:41.556 --> 23:43.251
Something like that.

23:43.597 --> 23:44.747
What do you mean?

23:44.795 --> 23:46.931
La Grange wasn't what it seemed.

23:48.069 --> 23:50.313
A lot of bad stuff happened here.

23:51.956 --> 23:53.774
This is me. I got to go.

23:54.052 --> 23:55.587
Linda.

23:57.400 --> 23:59.571
Do you know who killed Rosemary?

24:00.829 --> 24:03.401
- I have no idea.
- Wait.

24:06.462 --> 24:08.479
Look...

24:09.009 --> 24:10.571
Toby's gone now,

24:10.637 --> 24:12.579
and there could be more
if this keeps going.

24:12.660 --> 24:14.392
I don't understand what you mean.

24:14.677 --> 24:16.290
Just let it go.

24:19.005 --> 24:20.855
It's good to see you, Maddie.

24:38.827 --> 24:41.178
She said she nearly overdosed.

24:42.432 --> 24:44.826
Yeah. Well, maybe her life
just got complicated.

24:45.554 --> 24:47.712
No, I think it was about Rosemary.

24:48.304 --> 24:51.315
I never realized how much
her death affected everyone.

24:52.194 --> 24:54.266
A girl is murdered.

24:54.655 --> 24:56.460
The case became a national obsession.

24:56.546 --> 24:59.354
Of course it affected everyone.

25:00.007 --> 25:02.296
She said I should
stop asking questions.

25:02.421 --> 25:03.712
Maybe she's right, you know?

25:03.749 --> 25:06.150
Maybe Toby would still be alive
if I hadn't confronted him.

25:06.253 --> 25:08.012
Mm-mmm. No, that's not your fault.

25:08.968 --> 25:11.825
Listen, you deserve to find out
who killed Rosemary,

25:12.138 --> 25:14.072
because it wasn't you.

25:16.960 --> 25:19.882
- I'm never getting married.
- Sure, you will.

25:20.093 --> 25:22.647
<i>Someday, a handsome guy
is gonna kiss you</i>

25:22.684 --> 25:26.477
in a perfect way,
and you're gonna melt.

25:26.514 --> 25:27.624
[LAUGHS]

25:27.661 --> 25:29.419
I'm not really the melting type.

25:29.485 --> 25:31.874
[BOTH LAUGH]

25:31.911 --> 25:33.530
<i>MADELINE: Do you think
we'll always be friends?</i>

25:33.567 --> 25:34.921
<i>Even if we're old and...</i>

25:34.958 --> 25:36.358
married with kids?

25:36.416 --> 25:39.196
You kidding? Of course.
I'm moving in next door

25:39.233 --> 25:40.845
so our kids can be best friends, too.

25:40.906 --> 25:43.949
[BOTH LAUGHING]

25:45.544 --> 25:47.507
What are you thinking about?

25:49.296 --> 25:50.914
You.

25:52.609 --> 25:54.514
I'm thinking you're pretty great.

25:56.863 --> 25:58.702
Well, I think you're pretty great, too.

25:59.819 --> 26:04.236
♪ <i>I have been a spark ♪
♪ waiting for gasoline</i> ♪

26:05.382 --> 26:06.762
♪ <i>The aftermath</i> ♪

26:06.799 --> 26:09.639
♪ <i>When all is said and done</i> ♪

26:10.923 --> 26:12.506
♪ <i>Chain reaction</i> ♪

26:12.543 --> 26:15.553
♪ <i>Coming from the oxygen</i> ♪

26:15.836 --> 26:17.968
♪ <i>In my lungs.</i> ♪

26:18.082 --> 26:20.082
[INDISTINCT CHATTER ON VIDEO]

26:26.233 --> 26:27.567
Hey, how is it?

26:27.686 --> 26:29.218
It's like Kubrick and Fellini...

26:29.288 --> 26:31.013
if they were both lobotomized.

26:31.624 --> 26:34.030
It's hours of drinking and dancing,

26:34.067 --> 26:36.350
and one kid threw up, which made
four other kids throw up,

26:36.387 --> 26:38.218
and it's all shot with flair.

26:38.382 --> 26:39.688
What about our girl?

26:39.715 --> 26:41.842
CinderHella is barely in it.
Couple of cameos early,

26:41.879 --> 26:43.600
but nothing that's gonna work
for an alibi.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.968
This reminds me of my college days.

26:46.305 --> 26:48.455
Oh, yeah? Violet was a party girl?

26:48.492 --> 26:50.977
- Come on, how hard-core were you?
- You have no idea.

26:51.014 --> 26:53.194
- Come on, inquiring minds want to know.
- No.

26:53.401 --> 26:55.168
Wait. Pause the video.

26:56.140 --> 26:59.889
In the background there...
isn't that Grant Thargard?

27:03.898 --> 27:05.194
[BODIE SIGHS]

27:05.306 --> 27:06.764
<i>[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]</i>

27:08.127 --> 27:10.915
- Hello, Madeline.
- Were you lying in wait?

27:10.952 --> 27:12.194
No, I knew you'd be coming this way.

27:12.231 --> 27:13.655
I just wanted to have a word with you.

27:13.692 --> 27:15.531
It'll just take a moment.

27:15.611 --> 27:16.672
I'll get right to the point.

27:16.709 --> 27:18.985
You have to stop representing
Adele Meyerson.

27:19.091 --> 27:21.147
- Funny.
- I'm serious.

27:21.258 --> 27:23.900
Look, she is not one of your noble,

27:23.955 --> 27:26.547
wrongfully accused clients.

27:26.720 --> 27:28.866
I was part of the team
that worked the original trial,

27:28.938 --> 27:31.421
and DNA evidence
was tossed on a technicality,

27:31.460 --> 27:33.185
but it was a match.

27:33.222 --> 27:35.922
- She killed her mother.
- What are you doing here?

27:36.164 --> 27:37.804
Are your poll numbers sagging?

27:37.841 --> 27:39.249
Is this because I come
to your office once?

27:39.286 --> 27:40.734
Look, I'm here because I have
a fundamental

27:40.771 --> 27:42.974
obligation to protect the innocent

27:43.011 --> 27:45.709
and convict those who are not innocent.

27:46.144 --> 27:49.221
Our personal history aside,
I know when someone's guilty.

27:49.327 --> 27:51.360
Do you?

27:51.673 --> 27:54.060
Thank you, Gore. I'm good.

27:57.996 --> 27:59.604
Adele was belligerent.

27:59.710 --> 28:01.367
She was trying to order more booze,

28:01.404 --> 28:03.496
but her credit card was declined.

28:03.617 --> 28:07.360
She said, and I quote,
"My mom is such a bitch.

28:07.447 --> 28:08.896
I'm going to kill her."

28:09.608 --> 28:11.310
And then she left the party.

28:11.426 --> 28:13.076
Nothing further.

28:15.232 --> 28:18.140
That was a very lucid account
of what happened, Grant,

28:18.177 --> 28:19.591
very detailed.

28:19.779 --> 28:20.974
How do you remember so much

28:21.011 --> 28:23.345
when everyone was so wasted that night?

28:23.501 --> 28:26.951
- Not everyone. I was sober.
- Completely sober?

28:26.988 --> 28:29.873
Yup. I was the designated driver.

28:30.007 --> 28:32.365
Was driving my dad's Jag
that night, so...

28:32.599 --> 28:34.716
- didn't have a choice.
- MADELINE: Nice.

28:35.220 --> 28:38.588
I was just wondering
how you would explain this

28:38.625 --> 28:41.388
- to your dad.
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER ON VIDEO]

28:45.789 --> 28:48.189
That's you, right?

28:48.296 --> 28:50.740
Doing cocaine
all over the coffee table?

28:50.819 --> 28:51.943
[MURMURING]

28:52.225 --> 28:53.657
Grant...

28:54.016 --> 28:56.801
why did you lie
at Adele's original trial?

29:00.449 --> 29:02.568
The cops found the drugs on me.

29:02.693 --> 29:04.021
They told me if I didn't cooperate

29:04.058 --> 29:05.498
they were gonna
charge me with possession.

29:05.542 --> 29:06.925
So, to save yourself,

29:06.962 --> 29:09.805
you sent an innocent woman
to prison for murder.

29:09.842 --> 29:12.248
- Objection.
- Withdrawn.

29:12.833 --> 29:14.607
Think I'm done with this witness.

29:18.410 --> 29:21.162
In the words of the great
Paris Hilton, "That was hot."

29:21.199 --> 29:23.154
[LAUGHS]
There's something so satisfying

29:23.191 --> 29:25.253
about nailing liars on the stand.

29:25.290 --> 29:26.927
Only thing is he's got
a motive for lying,

29:26.964 --> 29:29.089
but not for killing Jane.
I don't think he did it.

29:29.565 --> 29:31.815
I know. We need a new suspect.

29:33.584 --> 29:35.158
Sorry, have we met?

29:35.378 --> 29:38.379
Not officially, but I've
been following your case.

29:39.084 --> 29:40.771
I'm Arthur Kauffman.

29:40.959 --> 29:43.466
I'm a criminal technology
professor at Northwestern.

29:43.538 --> 29:46.250
I've spent my career studying
the apex predator

29:46.287 --> 29:49.427
of the American urban ecosystem:
the serial killer.

29:49.473 --> 29:52.052
- Why are you following our case?
- I know Adele.

29:52.131 --> 29:53.232
I corresponded with her.

29:53.269 --> 29:55.676
I even visited her
in prison a few times.

29:55.913 --> 29:58.443
- What for?
- Actually, it ties in with what

29:58.480 --> 29:59.935
you were just talking about.

29:59.993 --> 30:02.401
A suspect? You have one?

30:03.124 --> 30:04.443
Possibly.

30:04.693 --> 30:07.994
I think Jane Meyerson was
murdered by a serial killer.

30:13.396 --> 30:14.772
ARTHUR: I remembered when Jane's case

30:14.809 --> 30:16.007
was all over the news.

30:16.044 --> 30:18.099
Honestly, I never
gave it much attention.

30:18.226 --> 30:21.927
My focus was always on...
Carter Leopold.

30:21.966 --> 30:23.051
The notorious blue blood

30:23.088 --> 30:25.068
accused of stalking
and killing five women.

30:25.118 --> 30:26.474
He was acquitted, found innocent.

30:26.511 --> 30:29.258
Because of sloppy police work
and sleazy defense counsel.

30:29.295 --> 30:31.029
- No offense.
- None taken.

30:31.131 --> 30:32.451
ARTHUR:
It wasn't until a few months ago

30:32.487 --> 30:33.802
when a student of mine wrote a paper

30:33.839 --> 30:35.514
on Jane Meyerson's murder that I

30:35.551 --> 30:37.865
began noticing several
striking similarities

30:37.902 --> 30:40.829
between Jane's case and
Leopold's known victims.

30:40.866 --> 30:42.021
They were all middle-aged women

30:42.058 --> 30:43.693
who had been stabbed multiple times.

30:43.763 --> 30:45.380
I contacted Adele right away.

30:45.417 --> 30:47.584
I started asking her
specific questions.

30:47.786 --> 30:49.721
I was then able to track Mr. Leopold

30:49.758 --> 30:51.685
using an algorithm I designed.

30:51.763 --> 30:54.855
An algorithm? You have a math
algorithm for solving murders?

30:54.922 --> 30:57.172
A mathematical model, more accurately.

30:57.209 --> 31:00.312
My students and I have been
amassing data on every murder

31:00.349 --> 31:03.045
occurring in the U.S.
over the last 40 years.

31:03.154 --> 31:05.435
Allow me to demonstrate.

31:08.898 --> 31:11.958
You enter the victim's age: 43.
Race: Caucasian.

31:11.995 --> 31:13.935
Sex: female. And so on.

31:14.006 --> 31:15.639
Next, we detail the crime scene:

31:15.676 --> 31:17.211
was the body found indoors?

31:17.248 --> 31:19.545
If so, was there signs of forced entry?

31:19.582 --> 31:20.672
Sexual assault?

31:20.709 --> 31:22.365
In Jane Meyerson's case,
the cause of death

31:22.402 --> 31:24.021
was multiple stab wounds.

31:24.147 --> 31:27.373
The program then assigns Jane's
case a seven-digit number,

31:27.473 --> 31:29.568
which then links to...

31:33.255 --> 31:36.099
Every related homicide
in the greater Chicago area.

31:36.136 --> 31:38.287
Yes. I'm almost convinced

31:38.324 --> 31:40.123
Jane was murdered by Carter Leopold.

31:40.160 --> 31:42.896
- Almost?
- One key element is missing.

31:43.027 --> 31:44.474
Leopold had a fixation.

31:44.511 --> 31:47.576
He required his victims
to ask to be killed.

31:47.613 --> 31:50.188
So he contacted them
using an e-mail scam.

31:50.279 --> 31:51.840
He signs each of his phishing e-mails

31:51.877 --> 31:53.859
with the initials "H.T.S."

31:53.973 --> 31:56.654
I believe that stands for
"Hunt, Torture, Stab."

31:56.765 --> 31:59.351
- Catchy.
- ARTHUR: If the recipient replies,

31:59.951 --> 32:02.191
he stalks and then kills her.

32:02.795 --> 32:04.482
There's no way we can know
if he killed Jane

32:04.519 --> 32:06.451
unless we access her e-mail account.

32:06.607 --> 32:08.834
Why didn't Adele mention
this theory to us?

32:08.871 --> 32:10.420
ARTHUR: She doesn't believe it herself.

32:10.532 --> 32:12.451
She probably doesn't want you
to think she's crazy.

32:12.498 --> 32:14.740
But I really think
there could be something here.

32:14.854 --> 32:16.771
Bodie, you think you can hack
into Jane's e-mail?

32:16.849 --> 32:18.766
Yeah, I'm all over it.

32:20.834 --> 32:22.935
MADELINE: Something about this
case just never made sense.

32:22.972 --> 32:24.880
No plausible alternative suspect.

32:24.917 --> 32:26.771
So now we have one.

32:31.018 --> 32:32.865
- You said you were making progress.
- [SIGHS]

32:32.902 --> 32:35.154
There's nothing there.
She didn't kill Rosemary Lynch.

32:35.245 --> 32:36.545
I thought she suspected her brother.

32:36.582 --> 32:37.873
She doesn't. I grilled her about that.

32:37.910 --> 32:40.355
Look, she's trying to find
the real killer, all right?

32:40.392 --> 32:42.725
And if she finds him or her,
that's the story.

32:42.824 --> 32:45.091
So you're saying this could
take months or years or never?

32:45.128 --> 32:46.919
- [PHONE VIBRATING]
- Yeah, that's what I'm saying.

32:47.520 --> 32:49.911
All right. Move on to something else.

32:52.119 --> 32:53.911
My name is Charles Lynch.

32:54.334 --> 32:57.505
My daughter Rosemary died
at the hands of a brutal killer.

32:57.716 --> 32:59.959
<i>Her murder devastated her community,</i>

33:00.037 --> 33:01.255
<i>her friends,</i>

33:01.292 --> 33:03.283
<i>and it destroyed my life.</i>

33:03.414 --> 33:05.598
<i>Gore Bellows says he's creating
Rosemary's Law</i>

33:05.635 --> 33:07.468
<i>to help the victims of crime.</i>

33:07.607 --> 33:09.924
<i>You know what you can
do for me, Mr. Bellows?</i>

33:10.170 --> 33:12.712
<i>You can find the person
who killed my daughter</i>

33:12.864 --> 33:15.549
<i>and stop using her name
for political gain.</i>

33:15.652 --> 33:18.670
<i>Evan Esteban-Miller
has dedicated his life</i>

33:18.707 --> 33:19.980
<i>to this community.</i>

33:20.123 --> 33:21.414
<i>I stand with him.</i>

33:21.570 --> 33:23.194
<i>Because he stands for us.</i>

33:23.339 --> 33:25.185
<i>I am Evan Esteban-Miller,</i>

33:25.222 --> 33:26.834
<i>and I approve...</i>

33:27.965 --> 33:30.799
I think that puts the stake
in Rosemary's Law.

33:31.042 --> 33:32.926
Then let's blanket the state with ads

33:32.963 --> 33:35.982
tying Esteban-Miller to
Detective Falcone's corruption.

33:36.019 --> 33:37.490
MAYFIELD: With what money?

33:37.527 --> 33:40.646
Call Zahn. apologize, beg.

33:40.683 --> 33:42.451
Or promise him everything he wants.

33:42.488 --> 33:44.811
Then stiff him once you're in office.

33:46.180 --> 33:47.724
Now, that I can live with.

33:48.453 --> 33:49.951
BODIE: I'm in.

33:53.326 --> 33:54.946
Enter password.

33:57.346 --> 33:59.685
"H.T.S." Let's search for that,
see if anything pops up here.

34:02.033 --> 34:03.265
Oh, wow.

34:03.545 --> 34:05.279
That looks like he
contacted her for months.

34:05.316 --> 34:06.434
Mm-hmm.

34:06.553 --> 34:07.959
MADELINE: And she responded.

34:07.996 --> 34:09.271
That fits the profile.

34:09.308 --> 34:11.745
- I'll work on Leopold's subpoena.
- MADELINE: Okay.

34:12.521 --> 34:13.980
Really nice work.

34:14.156 --> 34:16.568
[TEXT ALERT WHISTLES, DINGS]

34:18.018 --> 34:19.724
Oh, no. This isn't good.

34:19.804 --> 34:20.966
What?

34:21.024 --> 34:22.943
It's a news story about you.

34:23.114 --> 34:26.248
"Did Madeline Scott
drive friend to suicide?"

34:26.331 --> 34:28.795
- Great.
- "Sources close to Scott

34:28.831 --> 34:30.713
"reveal she remains
obsessed with solving

34:30.750 --> 34:32.224
"Rosemary Lynch's murder.

34:32.261 --> 34:34.804
Scott's prime suspects
include her brother."

34:35.927 --> 34:37.405
How would they know that?

34:37.523 --> 34:39.646
Well, it's the <i> Daily Post.</i>

34:42.475 --> 34:44.154
That's Dylan's paper.

34:46.282 --> 34:47.935
His name is in the byline.

34:48.371 --> 34:51.091
"Additional reporting by Dylan Pierce."

34:52.493 --> 34:53.841
He was using me.

34:53.927 --> 34:55.638
I am so sorry, Maddie.

35:00.071 --> 35:02.240
<i>JOE: It's the company's hard drive.</i>

35:02.357 --> 35:03.678
I gave the research to Amanda

35:03.715 --> 35:05.436
and she behaved like a
professional and wrote it up.

35:05.472 --> 35:06.513
You son of a bitch, I told you

35:06.550 --> 35:08.857
- I didn't want to do this.
- You slept with her, didn't you?

35:09.420 --> 35:11.591
Rule number one
in shtupping your sources:

35:11.750 --> 35:14.525
use the sex to get the story,
not to lose it.

35:17.287 --> 35:18.615
Go to hell.

35:18.791 --> 35:20.740
I quit.

35:21.208 --> 35:23.208
[PHONE RINGS]

35:30.122 --> 35:32.227
Hey. How you holding up?

35:32.810 --> 35:34.966
Totally fine. Busy.

35:35.146 --> 35:38.105
I know it sucks.
I thought Dylan was a keeper.

35:38.442 --> 35:39.779
No, I...

35:39.888 --> 35:41.427
Honestly, it was nothing.

35:41.916 --> 35:44.123
Seriously. I'm good.

35:44.779 --> 35:46.740
But you know I'm here
if you want to talk.

35:46.791 --> 35:49.234
I have a lot of experience
with men who disappoint,

35:49.271 --> 35:51.322
and you do not want
to bottle up that anger.

35:56.888 --> 35:59.009
- You ready to go?
- Yeah.

36:05.507 --> 36:07.357
Mr. Leopold, you were charged
with the murder

36:07.394 --> 36:09.594
of five women you met online,
is that correct?

36:09.631 --> 36:11.271
Objection. Relevance.

36:11.367 --> 36:14.359
Sustained. Mr. Leopold,
you don't have to answer that.

36:14.396 --> 36:15.701
You're not on trial here.

36:15.738 --> 36:17.037
I have nothing to hide.

36:17.074 --> 36:18.700
I was fully acquitted of all charges.

36:18.737 --> 36:20.970
The accusations against me
were unfounded.

36:21.341 --> 36:23.436
Well, you have plenty
of personal experience

36:23.473 --> 36:25.420
with false accusations,
don't you, Miss Scott?

36:25.472 --> 36:27.396
Absolutely. I'm representing

36:27.433 --> 36:29.677
a falsely accused client right now.

36:29.901 --> 36:31.170
Mr. Leopold, when did you

36:31.207 --> 36:33.388
first meet the victim, Jane Meyerson?

36:33.425 --> 36:34.641
Oh, I never met her.

36:34.759 --> 36:36.607
You mean you've
never met her in person.

36:36.644 --> 36:37.990
As opposed to on the Internet?

36:38.027 --> 36:39.573
I never met her
on the Internet, either.

36:39.610 --> 36:40.826
Is that right?

36:40.865 --> 36:43.740
I'd like to introduce you
to Defense Exhibit F.

36:44.083 --> 36:45.474
It's an e-mail

36:45.572 --> 36:47.724
sent from you to Jane Meyerson,

36:47.761 --> 36:49.857
dated February 17.

36:50.859 --> 36:53.610
It's the same day
Jane Meyerson was murdered.

36:54.085 --> 36:55.709
I did not write this e-mail.

36:55.834 --> 36:57.974
Well, the IP address
attached to the e-mail

36:58.011 --> 37:02.099
is registered to
1932 South Avalon Drive.

37:02.136 --> 37:04.373
- Isn't that where you live?
- Yes.

37:05.209 --> 37:06.576
But this is not me.

37:06.623 --> 37:07.959
I didn't send this woman an e-mail,

37:07.996 --> 37:09.436
and I certainly didn't kill her.

37:09.473 --> 37:11.029
Well, I'd be happy to
let the jury decide

37:11.066 --> 37:12.193
who killed Mrs. Meyerson.

37:12.230 --> 37:14.981
I'm just trying to establish
who sent her dozens

37:15.018 --> 37:16.629
of catfishing e-mails.

37:16.666 --> 37:20.279
Didn't you send the exact H.T.S....

37:20.316 --> 37:22.909
Hunt, Torture, Stab... e-mail

37:22.984 --> 37:25.539
to five other women
who were brutally stabbed

37:25.576 --> 37:28.232
the same way that Jane Meyerson
was brutally stabbed?

37:28.269 --> 37:31.435
Objection. I thought Mr. Leopold
wasn't on trial here.

37:31.472 --> 37:34.665
Overruled. I'd like to hear
his answer on this.

37:35.915 --> 37:37.357
I...

37:38.538 --> 37:40.762
- I plead the Fifth.
- Excuse me?

37:40.926 --> 37:42.732
[GALLERY MURMURING]

37:42.912 --> 37:44.701
Mr. Leopold, do you have
reason to believe

37:44.738 --> 37:46.571
that if you answer
my questions truthfully

37:46.608 --> 37:49.682
that you will be subject
to criminal prosecution?

37:49.719 --> 37:52.404
I don't know. I just know
I didn't write this e-mail.

37:52.441 --> 37:54.084
- And I don't understand...
- Because you stabbed

37:54.121 --> 37:55.905
Jane Meyerson the same way
that you stabbed

37:55.942 --> 37:57.366
those other five women.

37:57.403 --> 38:00.559
- I didn't do this. I swear.
- Objection. The witness is...

38:00.596 --> 38:03.591
Did you also mean to frame
the defendant, Adele Meyerson,

38:03.628 --> 38:05.490
for the murder of her own mother?

38:05.589 --> 38:07.435
Or was the sloppy police investigation

38:07.472 --> 38:10.045
- just a happy accident for you?
- Objection.

38:10.244 --> 38:11.827
Withdrawn.

38:13.626 --> 38:15.177
I think we're done here.

38:19.971 --> 38:21.529
What just happened?

38:21.661 --> 38:24.052
I think we just found
your mother's killer.

38:40.013 --> 38:41.140
Miss Meyerson.

38:41.177 --> 38:42.536
Please stand.

38:44.186 --> 38:46.685
Madam Foreperson, what say you?

38:46.800 --> 38:47.874
We, the jury,

38:47.911 --> 38:50.794
find the defendant, Adele Meyerson,

38:51.138 --> 38:53.560
not guilty of murder
in the first degree.

38:53.681 --> 38:55.464
JUDGE: Congratulations, Miss Meyerson.

38:55.501 --> 38:57.087
You are free to go.

38:57.160 --> 39:00.013
[MURMURING]

39:00.217 --> 39:01.419
Couldn't have done it without you.

39:01.456 --> 39:03.083
- Thanks.
- This is your victory, too.

39:03.149 --> 39:04.924
Thank you. Thank you.

39:10.242 --> 39:13.013
VIOLET: And now for
our fairy-tale ending.

39:13.293 --> 39:17.732
Our guests are Adele Meyerson
and Professor Arthur Kauffman.

39:17.843 --> 39:19.802
Adele, I will be honest,

39:20.333 --> 39:22.997
I could not have survived
the horror you endured.

39:23.124 --> 39:26.416
I really need to thank you guys
at the Injustice Defense Group

39:26.453 --> 39:28.529
for taking my case.

39:28.567 --> 39:30.150
For telling my story.

39:30.550 --> 39:33.607
And for talking to my hero,
Professor Kauffman.

39:34.153 --> 39:36.208
You people saved my life.

39:42.796 --> 39:44.896
That's great. Let's, um...

39:45.554 --> 39:46.696
Let's take five.

39:46.716 --> 39:48.234
I just have to use the bathroom.

39:48.281 --> 39:49.800
No problem.

39:54.219 --> 39:56.695
I was, uh, surprised
to hear from you again. I...

39:57.012 --> 39:58.817
Thank you. You had, uh,

39:58.854 --> 40:00.738
made your position pretty clear
last time.

40:00.934 --> 40:02.526
Positions change.

40:02.612 --> 40:04.093
And I realized that I wouldn't have

40:04.130 --> 40:06.889
any positions at all
if I didn't win this thing.

40:08.210 --> 40:10.210
And I'm gonna need a lot of money.

40:10.326 --> 40:11.648
[CHUCKLES]

40:11.731 --> 40:14.645
Well, we live in a post
Citizens United world my friend.

40:14.682 --> 40:16.332
I can give you all the money I want.

40:16.599 --> 40:20.007
And, uh, you know,
I'd be happy to, if...

40:20.505 --> 40:21.617
Well...

40:21.654 --> 40:23.704
after a standard review of all...

40:23.757 --> 40:25.289
relevant investigations,

40:25.326 --> 40:27.015
I suspect my staff will recommend

40:27.052 --> 40:28.635
that we discontinue any legal actions

40:28.672 --> 40:30.312
against your interests.

40:31.334 --> 40:34.476
Then let me respond by saying
I will do everything I can

40:34.513 --> 40:36.580
to get you seated in the AG's office.

40:36.778 --> 40:38.394
Thank you.

40:39.031 --> 40:41.617
I look forward to our time
together on the campaign trail.

40:42.388 --> 40:43.726
You're gonna campaign with me?

40:43.763 --> 40:45.004
Absolutely.

40:45.123 --> 40:46.414
I like you, Gore.

40:46.451 --> 40:48.001
And I adore Greta.

40:48.327 --> 40:50.273
So, I think we could have
a blast on the trail.

40:50.328 --> 40:53.070
- Oh. [CHUCKLES] Welcome aboard.
- Yeah.

40:53.149 --> 40:54.557
[BELLOWS CHUCKLES]

40:54.594 --> 40:58.132
I do have a, um... it's a bit
of an awkward question.

40:58.865 --> 41:00.390
Isabel Sanchez.

41:00.720 --> 41:01.995
She single?

41:03.451 --> 41:05.835
So that's why you want
to campaign with me.

41:05.872 --> 41:07.804
Guilty as charged, counselor.

41:08.026 --> 41:09.609
She's a real spitfire.

41:10.048 --> 41:11.992
Don't be offended
if she's not interested.

41:12.077 --> 41:14.796
[LAUGHS] No offense taken.

41:16.383 --> 41:17.915
VIOLET: Okay, so...

41:17.990 --> 41:19.702
I left them alone for a few minutes.

41:19.779 --> 41:21.887
The main mics were off,
but I'd left the room mics on.

41:21.953 --> 41:24.374
- Why?
- I had an instinct.

41:25.060 --> 41:26.819
A bad one.

41:30.895 --> 41:32.735
ADELE [ON RECORDING]: <i>I still
can't believe it worked.</i>

41:32.771 --> 41:34.273
ARTHUR: <i>I told you it would.</i>

41:34.448 --> 41:37.283
ADELE: <i>Planting those e-mails
on the computer was genius.</i>

41:39.407 --> 41:40.965
[ECHOING]: <i>You're my
brilliant professor.</i>

41:41.117 --> 41:43.050
I love you so much.

41:43.208 --> 41:44.590
ADELE: I love you, too.

41:44.687 --> 41:46.054
Damn.

41:46.165 --> 41:48.273
Adele and Kauffman were in it together.

41:48.656 --> 41:50.046
Bellows was right.

41:50.171 --> 41:52.554
Adele was guilty and we
just got her out of prison.

41:52.777 --> 41:55.109
So, we're just gonna
take these... these tapes

41:55.146 --> 41:56.562
to the police, right?

41:56.599 --> 41:58.152
EASY: No. We got her acquitted.

41:58.189 --> 41:59.999
She can't be tried again.
Double jeopardy.

42:00.109 --> 42:02.531
Plus, Bellows will crucify us
for defending the guilty.

42:02.593 --> 42:04.163
He'll hammer it in his campaign slogans

42:04.200 --> 42:05.499
and get himself elected.

42:05.634 --> 42:07.318
Man, they totally played us.

42:07.355 --> 42:08.880
It's diabolical.

42:09.208 --> 42:11.600
That CinderHella is good.

42:11.718 --> 42:13.273
MADELINE: And the cops
will go after Leopold

42:13.310 --> 42:14.601
and they'll find out he didn't do this.

42:14.638 --> 42:16.476
We can still get this Professor Con Job

42:16.513 --> 42:18.163
for accessory after the fact, right?

42:18.200 --> 42:19.825
Attorney-client privilege.

42:19.895 --> 42:22.296
We can't implicate him
without implicating her.

42:22.447 --> 42:24.296
We can't do anything. We're screwed.

42:26.469 --> 42:28.561
VIOLET: <i>It is the ethical
obligation of every lawyer</i>

42:28.598 --> 42:31.390
<i>to mount a compelling defense
for their client.</i>

42:31.462 --> 42:34.382
Of course we hope to exonerate
only the innocent.

42:34.419 --> 42:36.793
<i>But sometimes the system fails</i>

42:36.830 --> 42:38.547
<i>and the guilty are set free.</i>

42:39.004 --> 42:41.921
Now, lawyers are forbidden
to betray their clients,

42:41.958 --> 42:43.941
<i>innocent or guilty.</i>

42:44.368 --> 42:47.293
<i>But for those of us who aren't lawyers,</i>

42:47.429 --> 42:50.273
<i>we know that if a person
gets away with a crime,</i>

42:50.361 --> 42:52.554
there's a good chance
they'll commit another.

42:53.242 --> 42:55.110
<i>And when they do,</i>

42:55.714 --> 42:57.773
<i>we will be right there to catch them.</i>

43:03.976 --> 43:05.343
Hey.

43:05.423 --> 43:06.749
Listen, I've been trying to call you.

43:06.786 --> 43:10.117
I am so sorry, okay?
Joe ran that story, not me.

43:10.199 --> 43:11.499
I tried to get him to stop it...

43:11.590 --> 43:12.889
[GRUNTS]

